line_1: WHat if serenely blest with Calms I swam
line_2: Pactolus! in thy golden Sanded stream?

line_1: How strange you look'd, how awkwardly you swam.
line_2: But think, Ingrate, when first you hither came,

line_1: And wept to hear his Moan; the Nereids swam
line_2: While thus Pasinthas plain'd, the Dolphins came,
